---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Hobbes Digital"
  description="A small marketing team in Singapore. We work with small business owners to build steady, predictable customer flow — without the agency overhead."
>

  <!-- Page hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">About us</span>
      <h1>A small team that does the work.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        There's no account manager layer here. The people you talk to
        are the people running your marketing — the same person who
        wrote the strategy is the one running your ads next Tuesday.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="about-mission">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-mission-inner">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why we exist</span>
        <h2>
          Small business owners in Singapore have been burned by agencies
          that over-promise. We built something different.
        </h2>
        <p>
          Most marketing agencies are structured around winning accounts and
          managing up. A junior team does the work; a senior team manages
          the relationship. The result is expensive, slow, and often
          disconnected from how a business actually runs.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're built the other way. Small engagements, senior people,
          real accountability. You know what we're doing, why we're
          doing it, and what changes if it's not working.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="about-principles">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-divider">
        <span class="eyebrow">How we work</span>
      </div>
      <div class="about-principles-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>Plain language, always.</h3>
          <p>
            We don't have a deck full of frameworks to explain why things
            cost what they cost. Everything we do has a plain-English
            rationale you can read in five minutes and hand to anyone in
            your business.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>One number we care about.</h3>
          <p>
            For most clients, it's revenue. For some, it's repeat customers
            or qualified leads. We pick one metric with you at the start and
            report against it every month, honestly.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>No long contracts.</h3>
          <p>
            Engagements run quarterly with a written checkpoint. If the
            results aren't there, we say so first — and we either fix the
            plan or part ways. Your call, either way.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who we work with -->
  <section class="about-fit">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-fit-inner">
        <div class="section-divider">
          <span class="eyebrow">Who we work with</span>
        </div>
        <h2>We work best with owners, not committees.</h2>
        <p>
          Our clients are typically the person who built the business —
          F&B operators, retail shop owners, clinic founders, service
          businesses scaling to their first team of ten. They're time-poor,
          often non-marketers, and done with agencies that can't give them
          a straight answer about whether the spend is working.
        </p>
        <p>
          If that sounds like you, <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>.
          We read every message ourselves and reply within one business day.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Ready when you are</p>
      <h2>
        Tell us about your business.<br />
        <em>We'll tell you what we'd do.</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        No pressure, no pitch deck. A 30-minute conversation, and a written
        note from us afterwards either way.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Start a conversation →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
